Rating: 1
I had high hopes for this sandwich but it was very bland to me. I even used a Costco rotisserie chicken which is full of flavor. Maybe more lime juice, more jalapeno.

Rating: 0
These sandwiches are a HUGE hit with my family. We have them all the time and people beg me for the recipe. We have also bought roasted red peppers when we don't have time to make our own, and we use sourdough bread from the local bakery. Two other changes that I'd recommend trying are substituting MAPLE yogurt for the sour cream (this gives the spread a lovely, slight sweetness) and using "Lemonaise" (from The Ojai Cook) instead of regular mayonnaise. If you are out of mayo, please beware of using Miracle Whip. I did that once and it completely ruined the spread. It really needs authentic mayo. I am not usually a fan of mayonnaise, but as an ingredient for this recipe, some decent mayo is a must.

