I pack my own lunches to work and this recipe was delicious! I didn't process the ingredients since I didn't want to clean a processor just for one sandwich and didn't know if I would like the recipe or not. Therefore I diced all the ingredients. I used leftover grilled chicken I had for dinner. (I threw the pepper on the grill as well.) I also added Sriracha (sp) sauce to the mayo and didn't have so omitted the sour cream. I toasted sour dough bread and proceeded to make the sandwich. I took a taste bite and wasn't impressed. I wrapped it up and stuck it in the fridge for lunch next day. Wow! The stay in the fridge infused all the flavors! It's definitely a keeper. I love to cook so never really follow the recipe but rather use it as a guide and add whatever I have. I'm curious to follow this recipe as instructed now to see if it'll taste even better. Still have some leftover chicken so will be making it again tonight for my boyfriend's lunch tomorrow.

