I also got lots of complements on this from the younger generation of my household. I thought the almonds sounded/would be odd in mayonaise, but ground up they gave a lovely subtle crunchiness. I made the following changes: grilled the chicken, since it is August, used roasted red peppers from a jar to save time, and didn't add sour cream since we keep kosher and don't mix milk with meat. THere was not the slightest hint of bitterness to the mayonaise, so perhaps that was from the sour cream. Served this with an Israeli salad- finely chopped cucumbers, tomatoes, red onions, carrots with a little oil and vinegar, and a peach pie at Ravinia, the outdoor summer home of the Chicago Symphony Orchestra, where everyone picnics and tries to outdo the next with elegant food and wine. We didn't have wine, flowers, and candles on a little table like our neighbors, but I felt suitably well cuisined.

