I shamefully added a couple of teaspoons of sugar to augment appeal to the masses. Without it, the relish did seem a little tart/bitter. The sandwiches were wonderful and received rave reviews. Flavorful and wonderful combination of ingredients. A good quality bread, of course, is a must. I bought a good dense white sourdough loaf which was presliced from my local all-organic-make-eveything-from-scratch-everyday baker. (If you do not have one of these in your area, you are missing something!) I served these sandwiches for a large teenage cast party, and they were some of the very first items to be gobbled up... the hotdogs and Sloppy Joe's were barely touched. So much for teenage sterotypes: I learned many of them actually have a hankering for gourmet delights.

